INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3500','letter','1777-09-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THERE has been a very general apprehension during the last week, that a general action would happen as on yesterday, but we hear of none.','ltr_jod3500.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3501','letter','1777-09-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Mr. Howe\'s army is at Chester, about fifteen miles from this town. General Washington\'s is over the Schuylkill, awaiting the flank of Mr. Howe\'s army.','ltr_jod3501.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3502','letter','1777-09-30','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','the Congress were alarmed in their beds by a letter from Mr. Hamilton, one of General Washington\'s family, that the enemy was in possession of the ford over the Schuylkill','ltr_jod3502.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3503','letter','1777-10-07','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','One thing is now becoming more and more certain every day, that is, that our people will and do fight. And although they make a clumsy hand of it, yet they do better and better.','ltr_jod3503.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3504','letter','1777-10-15','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Government and law in the States, large taxation, and strict discipline in our armies, are the only things wanting as human means. ','ltr_jod3504.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3505','letter','1777-10-24','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','News I am afraid to write, be cause I never know, until it is too late, what is true.','ltr_jod3505.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3506','letter','1777-10-25','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','As to news we are yet in a painful suspense about affairs at the northward, but from Philadelphia, we have accounts that are very pleasing.','ltr_jod3506.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3507','letter','1777-10-26','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The forts at Province Island and Redbank have been defended with a magnanimity which will give our country a reputation in Europe.','ltr_jod3507.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3508','letter','1777-10-28','Yorktown','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','WE have been three days soaking and poaching in the heaviest rain that has been known for several years','ltr_jod3508.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3509','letter','1777-12-15','Portsmouth','NH','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have had many opportunities, in the course of this journey, to observe how deeply rooted our righteous cause is in the minds of the people ; and could write you many anecdotes in proof of it.','ltr_jod3509.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3511','letter','1778-04-25','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','If human nature could be made happy by anything that can please the eye, the ear, the taste, or any other sense, or passion, or fancy, this country would be the region for happiness.','ltr_jod3511.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3512','letter','1778-06-03','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','It would be endless to attempt a description of this country. It is one great garden. Nature and art have conspired to render every thing here delightful.','ltr_jod3512.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3513','letter','1778-06-16','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','We long to hear from America the ratification of the treaty with France, the captivity of General Clinton\'s army, and of Lord Howe\'s fleet.','ltr_jod3513.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3514','letter','1778-09-23','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','A VERY idle, vain conversation at a dinner has produced you this letter from a venerable old lady in this neighborhood, the wife of Monsieur Grand the banker. ','ltr_jod3514.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3515','letter','1778-11-06','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','My anxiety for you and for the public is not diminished by time or distance. The great number of accidental disappointments in the course of the last summer are afflicting.','ltr_jod3515.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3516','letter','1778-11-27','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Europe is the dullest place in the world. No news but the lies which the emissaries of England are making and spreading in every part.','ltr_jod3516.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3517','letter','1778-12-02','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Draw for more as you may have occasion. But make them give you gold and silver for your bills.','ltr_jod3517.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3518','letter','1778-12-18','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have written several answers ; but upon a review, they appeared to be such as I could not send. One was angry, another was full of grief, and the third with melancholy, so that I burnt them all.','ltr_jod3518.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3519','letter','1778-12-27','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Last night I walked to Paris and saw the illumination for the birth of the princess Maria Theresa Charlotte, Fille du Roi. Splendid indeed !','ltr_jod3519.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3520','letter','1778-12-30','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','WE wait, and wait, and wait forever, without any news from America. We get nothing but what comes from England and to other people here, and they make it as they please.','ltr_jod3520.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3521','letter','1779-01-01','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I WISH you a happy new year and many happy years, and all the blessings of life. Who knows but this year may be more prosperous for our country than any we have seen ?','ltr_jod3521.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3522','letter','1779-02-09','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The character and situation in which I am here, and the situation of public affairs absolutely forbid my writing freely. I must be excused.','ltr_jod3522.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3523','letter','1779-02-13','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have received intelligence much more agreeable than that of a removal to Holland ; I mean that of being reduced to a private citizen, which gives me more pleasure than you can imagine.','ltr_jod3523.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3524','letter','1779-02-20','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','It would be an easy thing for me to ruin you and your children by an indiscreet letter, and what is more, it would be easy to throw our country into convulsions. For God\'s sake never reproach me again with not writing or with writing scrips.','ltr_jod3524.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3525','letter','1779-02-20','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','A NEW commission has arrived by which the Dr. is sole minister. Mr. Lee continues commissioner for Spain, but I am reduced to the condition of a private citizen.','ltr_jod3525.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3526','letter','1779-02-21','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The expense of my son here is greater than I ever imagined. Although his company is almost all the pleasure I have in life, yet I should not have brought him if I had known the expense.','ltr_jod3526.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3527','letter','1779-02-27','Passy','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I went to Saint Denis, a little village about eight miles from this place, where are the tombs of all the kings and queens. The statues of all lie in state in marble.','ltr_jod3527.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3528','letter','1779-05-14','Orient','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','By the gracious invitation of the King, I am now to take passage in his frigate, the Sensible, with his new Ambassador to America, the Chevalier de la Luzerne.','ltr_jod3528.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3529','letter','1779-11-13','Boston','MA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','It is proposed to sail tomorrow ; perhaps, however, it may not be till next day.','ltr_jod3529.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3530','letter','1779-12-11','Ferrol','','ESP','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','As the frigate will probably not get from this place these two months, I must go by land to Paris, which I suppose is a journey of between three and four hundred leagues.','ltr_jod3530.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3531','letter','1779-12-12','Ferrol','','ESP','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE French consul had agreed to carry me, Mr. Dana, Mr. Allen, and my three children and our three servants, this day to Corunna, which is about five leagues from this place, by water','ltr_jod3531.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3532','letter','1779-12-16','Corunna','','ESP','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The distance is about twenty miles by land, over high mountains and bad roads. You would have been diverted to have seen us all mounted upon our mules and marching in train.','ltr_jod3532.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3533','letter','1780-01-16','Bilboa','','ESP','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','WE arrived here last night, all alive, but all very near sick with violent colds taken on the road for want of comfortable accommodations.','ltr_jod3533.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3534','letter','1780-02-16','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The English bounce a great deal about obtaining seven thousand troops from the petty German princes and ten thousand from Ireland to send to America, but this is only a repetition of their annual gasconade.','ltr_jod3534.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3535','letter','1780-02-23','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE children made me a visit to-day, and went with me to dine with my old friends, the two Abbes, whom you have often heard me mention, Chalut and Arnoux','ltr_jod3535.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3536','letter','1780-00-00','','','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Since my arrival this time, I have driven about Paris more than I did before. The rural scenes around this town are charming. The public walks, gardens, &c., are extremely beautiful.','ltr_jod3536.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3537','letter','1780-00-00','','','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','YESTERDAY we went to see the garden of the King, Jardin du Roi, and his cabinet of natural history, cabinet d histoire naturelle. The cabinet of natural history is a great collection of metals, minerals, shells, insects, birds, beasts, fishes and precious stones.','ltr_jod3537.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3538','letter','1780-06-17','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I YESTERDAY received a letter of the 26th of April from brother Cranch, for which I thank him and will answer as soon as possible. He tells me you have drawn a little bill upon me.','ltr_jod3538.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3539','letter','1780-09-15','Amsterdam','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have sent you some things by Captain Davis, but he has no arms and I fear they will be lost by capture. I sent things by the Alliance.','ltr_jod3539.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3540','letter','1780-12-18','Amsterdam','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I HAVE this morning sent Mr. Thaxter with my two sons to Leyden, there to take up their residence for some time, and there to pursue their studies of Latin and Greek under the excellent masters, and there to attend lectures of the celebrated professors, in that university.','ltr_jod3540.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3541','letter','1781-12-02','Amsterdam','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I avoided saying any thing about Charles to save you the anxiety, which I fear you will now feel in its greatest severity, a long time. I thought he would go directly home in a short passage','ltr_jod3541.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3542','letter','1781-12-18','Amsterdam','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The King of England consoles his people under all their dis graces, disasters and dismal prospects, by telling them that they are brave and free. It is a pity for him that he did not allow the Americans to be so seven years ago.','ltr_jod3542.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3543','letter','1782-07-25','Hague','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','IN this country, as in all others, men are much addicted to \"hobby horses\" These nags are called in the language of the Dutch \"Liefhebbery\" as they are called in French \"Marotte\" I had rather ride a Dutch hobby horse than an English one, or a French.','ltr_jod3543.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3544','letter','1782-08-31','Hague','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','how much more luxurious it would be to me to d ne upon roast beef with Parson Smith, Dr. Tufts, or Norton Quincy ! or upon rusticoat potatoes with Portia! Ah ! Oh ! hi, ho, hum, and her daughter and sons !','ltr_jod3544.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3545','letter','1782-09-17','Hague','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','It is now five months since my public reception here, but we have not yet learned that any news of it has arrived in America.','ltr_jod3545.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3546','letter','1782-12-04','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','YOUR proposal of coming to Europe has long and tenderly affected me. The dangers and inconveniences are such, and a European life would be so dis agreeable to you, that I have suffered a great deal of anxiety in reflecting upon it.','ltr_jod3546.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3547','letter','1782-12-28','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I DARE say there is not a lady in America treated with a more curious dish of politics than is contained in the enclosed papers.','ltr_jod3547.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3548','letter','1783-02-18','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have written to Congress a resignation, but I foresee there will not be a speedy decision upon it, and I shall be left in a state of suspense that will be intolerable.','ltr_jod3548.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3549','letter','1783-02-27','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','No. Let us live in our own country, and in our own way, educate our children to be good for some thing. Upon no consideration whatever would I have any of my children educated in Europe.','ltr_jod3549.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3550','letter','1783-05-30','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','HERE I am out of all patience. Not a word from America. The British ministry lingering on. Mr. Hartley uncertain what to do. No regulation of commerce agreed on. No definitive treaty of peace signed','ltr_jod3550.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3551','letter','1783-04-08','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','WHAT would I not give for an arrival from America, or for certain advice from London of the appointment of a ministry, or for the arrival here of a minister to sign the definitive treaty ?','ltr_jod3551.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3552','letter','1783-06-19','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I know not whether my resignation is accepted, and consequently can give you no conjecture when I shall be able to get away.','ltr_jod3552.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3553','letter','1783-09-07','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Mr. Laurens has leave to go home, and Mr. Dana is gone, so that there remain in service only Mr. Franklin, Mr. Jay, and myself. In these circumstances I must stay another winter.','ltr_jod3553.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3554','letter','1783-09-10','Paris','','FRA','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','WE have received from Congress a resolution by which we are to be empowered to negotiate a treaty of commerce with Great Britain, myself, Mr. Franklin and Mr. Jay.','ltr_jod3554.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3555','letter','1783-11-08','London','','ENG','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I HAVE this day, by special permission from their majesties, obtained by Mr. West, the painter, who with Mr. Copley does so much honor to our country, seen the apartments in the Queen\'s house','ltr_jod3555.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3556','letter','1784-07-26','Hague','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','YOUR letter of the 23d Has made me the happiest man upon earth. I am twenty years younger than I was yesterday. It is a cruel mortification to me that I cannot go to meet you in London','ltr_jod3556.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3557','letter','1786-12-25','London','','ENG','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','An old man, you see, may comfort himself with such a virgin as much as David did with Abishag, and not give the least jealousy even to his wife, the smallest grief to his children, or any scandal to the world.','ltr_jod3557.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3558','letter','1786-12-27','London','','ENG','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The news from Boston is very well. The court has set at Cambridge in great pomp, guarded by three thousand men and a train of artillery.','ltr_jod3558.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3559','letter','1788-03-11','Amsterdam','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I hope you will have every thing ready, that by the twenty-first or second of March, we may set off together for Falmouth from London.','ltr_jod3559.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3560','letter','1788-03-14','Amsterdam','','NED','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Mr. Jefferson is so anxious to obtain money here to enable him to discharge some of the most urgent demands upon the United States, and preserve their credit from bankruptcy for two years longer','ltr_jod3560.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3561','letter','1788-12-02','Braintree','MA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','My love to our children, and respects and regards wherever you please. Don t be uneasy on account of your family here, nor in haste to come home before a good opportunity presents.','ltr_jod3561.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3562','letter','1789-04-19','Rye','NY','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','We arrived at this house last night (Saturday), shall rest here to-day, and go into New York to-morrow.','ltr_jod3562.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3563','letter','1789-05-14','New York','NY','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','If you think it best, leave Thomas at college, but I pray you to come on with Charles, as soon as possible.','ltr_jod3563.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3564','letter','1793-01-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have the same aversion to the multiplication of banks, and the same apprehension of their pernicious tendency, as you express. But so many people live upon them that they will have their course.','ltr_jod3564.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3565','letter','1793-01-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have received all the votes from all the States. It is known that Georgia voted with North Carolina, Virginia and New York ; and Kentucky voted for Jefferson.','ltr_jod3565.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3566','letter','1793-01-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I cannot say that my desire of fame increases. It has been strong in some parts of my life, but never so strong as my love of honesty.','ltr_jod3566.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3567','letter','1793-01-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Mrs. Washington requests me to present to you her very particular regards. Many other ladies do the same.','ltr_jod3567.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3568','letter','1793-02-12','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have now to congratulate you on the arrival of your son and daughter and two grandsons, in fine health, at New York. They have done wisely to fly from the evil to come in Europe','ltr_jod3568.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3569','letter','1793-02-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The fermentation in Europe distresses me, lest it should take a turn which may involve us in many difficulties. Our neutrality will be a very delicate thing to maintain','ltr_jod3569.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3570','letter','1793-03-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I will never travel but by the stage, nor live at the seat of government but at lodgings, while they give me so despicable an allowance. Shiver my jib and start my planks if I do.','ltr_jod3570.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3571','letter','1793-12-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The President\'s speech will show you an abundance of serious business which we have before us. Mr. Jefferson called on me last night, and informed me that to-day we should have the whole budget of foreign affairs','ltr_jod3571.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3572','letter','1793-12-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','If a suitable season should occur for ploughing, our men may plough ; if not, they may leave it till spring, I like your plan very well ','ltr_jod3572.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3573','letter','1794-01-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The news from France, so glorious for the French army, is celebrated in loud peals of festivity, and elevates the spirits of the enemies of government among us more than it ought, for it will not answer their ends.','ltr_jod3573.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3574','letter','1794-01-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The prospects of this country are gloomy, but the situation of all Europe is calamitous beyond all former examples.','ltr_jod3574.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3575','letter','1794-01-12','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','KNOWING your taste for political speculations, I send you a couple of pamphlets for your amusement.','ltr_jod3575.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3576','letter','1794-01-22','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I AM weary of this scene of dulness. We have done nothing and shall do nothing this session, which ought to be done, unless we should appropriate a sufficient sum of money for treating with the Algerines.','ltr_jod3576.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3577','letter','1794-02-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','So ! the tables are turned on the French faction ! and the English faction will exult, in their turn, in the prospect of the West India Islands','ltr_jod3577.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3578','letter','1794-02-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Our allies, our only allies, as the demi crazies pathetically call them, have completed their system by turning all their churches into Je ne seals quoi','ltr_jod3578.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3579','letter','1794-02-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Poor Genet, I fear, is undone. Bad as his conduct has been, I cannot but pity him. What will become of him, I know not. The name of his successor is Fauchet.','ltr_jod3579.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3580','letter','1794-03-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have again been unfortunate at sea. The vessel in which I shipped my grass seeds and two barrels of rye flour for you, has been run down and sunk in the river by a large ship.','ltr_jod3580.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3581','letter','1794-03-12','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The Boston town meeting, as it terminated, did a service to the public. If government must be affronted or intimidated by popular clubs and partial meetings of the people, it is a pity that our cities are not all as capable as Boston of discussing great questions.','ltr_jod3581.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3582','letter','1794-04-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','A violent measure has been proposed in the House, to sequester all debts due from American citizens to British subjects. Such a motion will do no honor to our country.','ltr_jod3582.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3583','letter','1794-04-03','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','There are so many wild projects and motions, and so many to support them, that I am become of more importance than usual, in the opinion of the soundest part of the community.','ltr_jod3583.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3584','letter','1794-04-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The southern men have art enough to dupe northern ones to bring forward measures, that the northern part may have the odium of bringing on a war.','ltr_jod3584.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3585','letter','1794-04-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','One firebrand is scarcely quenched before another is thrown in ; and if the sound part of the community is not uncommonly active and attentive to support us, we shall be drawn off from our neutral ground and involved in incomprehensible evils.','ltr_jod3585.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3586','letter','1794-04-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Vox populi, vox Dei, they say, and so it is, sometimes ; but it is some times the voice of Mahomet, of Caesar, of Catiline, the Pope and the Devil.','ltr_jod3586.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3587','letter','1794-04-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','SENATE has been three days in debate upon the appointment of Mr. Jay to go to London. It has this day been determined in his favor eighteen versus eight.','ltr_jod3587.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3588','letter','1794-05-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Those whose principles are the same with mine, whose views of public good coincide with mine, say that if we keep together, we shall succeed to the end of the session as we have hitherto done, in keeping off all the most pernicious projects.','ltr_jod3588.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3589','letter','1794-05-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','WE go on as usual, Congress resolving one thing and the democratical societies resolving the contrary ; the President doing what is right, and clubs and mobs re solving it to be all wrong.','ltr_jod3589.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3590','letter','1794-05-17','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE long continuance of the session, and the uncommon heat and drought of the weather, have made this to me an unpleasant spring, and to increase my mortification, I have this week received no letter from you.','ltr_jod3590.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3591','letter','1794-05-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I SHALL enclose with this some letters between Randolph and Hammond, which will show you how quarrelsome they are. Poor fellows !','ltr_jod3591.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3592','letter','1794-05-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','IT is proper that I should apprize you that the President has it in contemplation to send your son to Holland, that you may recollect yourself and prepare for the event.','ltr_jod3592.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3593','letter','1794-11-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I find that gentlemen cannot conveniently leave their plantations and professions in season to be here sooner. A fortnight has been already lost and we have no certainty of making a Senate on Monday.','ltr_jod3593.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3594','letter','1794-11-17','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The Presbyterian congregation in Market street have taken down their old meeting house and erected a new one in the same place, much larger, higher, more light, airy and elegant.','ltr_jod3594.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3595','letter','1794-11-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I pore upon my family at Quincy, my children in Europe, and my children and grandchildren in New York, till I am melancholy, and wish myself a private man.','ltr_jod3595.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3596','letter','1794-11-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','IT is a common observation of old people, that as they advance in life, time appears to run off faster, and the year grows shorter. I cannot, I am sure, say the same of the time which has passed of late.','ltr_jod3596.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3597','letter','1794-12-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','This session of Congress is the most innocent I ever knew. We have done no harm.','ltr_jod3597.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3598','letter','1794-12-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','the time seems longer to me than ever any time did in America. The business of Congress this session is dulness, flatness, and insipidity itself.','ltr_jod3598.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3599','letter','1795-01-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I WISH you a happy new year, and a repetition of happy new years as long as time shall endure','ltr_jod3599.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3600','letter','1795-01-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','To a heart that loves praise so well, and receives so little of it, your letter is like laudanum, which Mr. Henry the senator, says, is the Divinity itself.','ltr_jod3600.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3601','letter','1795-01-29','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE public prints announce the death of my old, esteemed friend General Roberdeau, whose virtues in heart-searching times endeared him to Philadelphia and to his country.','ltr_jod3601.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3602','letter','1795-02-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The enclosed postscript to Dunlap will show you that the expectation of a treaty hourly to arrive, will not allow me to leave my chair till the fourth of March.','ltr_jod3602.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3603','letter','1795-02-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','This month has been all unpleasant weather, but none severe. You have had a north-east storm, I perceive, which raised the tides, but I hope, brought in a fresh and abundant supply of seaweed.','ltr_jod3603.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3604','letter','1795-06-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE Senate assembled yesterday at eleven, twenty- five members present. The new senators were sworn, and a committee waited on the President','ltr_jod3604.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3605','letter','1795-06-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE Senate are now in possession of the budget. It is a bone to gnaw for the aristocrats as well as the democrats','ltr_jod3605.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3606','letter','1795-06-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Moderation, however, is approved only by the moderate, who are commonly but a few. The many commonly delight in some thing more piquant and lively.','ltr_jod3606.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3607','letter','1795-06-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I went out to him and found that he wanted to enquire of me concerning a young lady of amiable manners and elegant education, whom Mr. Law and Mr. Greenleaf had found in Maryland, in great distress and a little disarranged','ltr_jod3607.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3608','letter','1795-06-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','He gave me many details of affairs in France ; a gloomy picture of the reign of terror, and a smiling one of the present reign of moderation ; but he is not without inquietude on the subject of a constitution.','ltr_jod3608.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3609','letter','1795-12-28','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Mrs. Adams, your new daughter, behaves prettily in her new sphere. I dined with them one day, and promised to take my lodgings with them the next time. Mrs. Adams showed me an elegant bed, which she politely said she had made up for me.','ltr_jod3609.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3610','letter','1796-01-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The President appears great in Randolph\'s vindication throughout, excepting that he wavered about signing the treaty, which he ought not to have done one moment.','ltr_jod3610.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3611','letter','1796-01-20','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THIS is one of my red letter days. It is the anniversary of the signature of the declaration of an armistice between the United States and Great Britain in 1783. There are several of these days in my calendar, which I recollect as they pass in review, but which nobody else remembers.','ltr_jod3611.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3612','letter','1796-01-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The southern gentry are playing, at present, a very artful game, which I may develope to you in confidence hereafter, under the seal of secrecy.','ltr_jod3612.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3613','letter','1796-01-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','YESTERDAY I came to the Senate, as usual on a Monday morning pleasing my imagination and my heart with the hope and expectation of a letter from my dearest friend. No letter for the Vice President!','ltr_jod3613.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3614','letter','1796-02-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','IT is Monday, the time to expect the eastern mail. Other men have letters, I have none. Humiliated and mortified, and, at the same time, irritated, I feel sometimes a disposition to abuse the post offices','ltr_jod3614.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3615','letter','1796-02-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I don t love slight, neglect, contempt, disgrace, nor insult, more than others. Yet I believe I have firmness of mind enough to bear it like a man, a hero, and a philosopher.','ltr_jod3615.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3616','letter','1796-02-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','There is a Dr. somebody here from Connecticut, who pretends, with an instrument made of some kind of metal or composition of metals, by a sort of mesmerian rubbing, or stroking, or conjuration, to cure rheumatisms, headaches, pleurisies, and I know not what.','ltr_jod3616.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3617','letter','1796-02-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The subject which you think will excite all their feelings is well known to every body in public life, but is talked of by nobody but in confidence.','ltr_jod3617.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3618','letter','1796-02-20','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','My mother\'s relief from her fears respecting her arm is a great pleasure to me. I hope to see her in good health in June. Have you given her my barrel of flour ?','ltr_jod3618.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3619','letter','1796-02-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I DINED yesterday with Mr. Madison. Mrs. Madison is a fine woman, and her two sisters are equally so.','ltr_jod3619.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3620','letter','1796-03-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','YESTERDAY the President sent his carriage for me to go with the family to the theatre. The Rage and the Spoiled Child were the two pieces. It rained and the house was not full.','ltr_jod3620.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3621','letter','1796-03-12','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I DINED yesterday with Mr. Burr, who lives here in style. A number of members of the House, the Speaker Mr. Dayton, among the rest.','ltr_jod3621.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3622','letter','1796-03-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I COVET the harp of Amphion. What would I not give for the harp of Amphion ?','ltr_jod3622.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3623','letter','1796-03-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I cannot see a ray of hope before June. If the House should be frenzical, we must sit till next March, and leave it to the people to decide by choosing a new President, Senate and House','ltr_jod3623.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3624','letter','1796-03-25','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','After dinner the gentlemen drew off after the ladies, and left me alone with the President in close conversation. He detained me there till nine o clock, and was never more frank and open upon politics.','ltr_jod3624.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3625','letter','1796-04-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I am so fatigued and disgusted with the insipidity of this dull life, that I am half of a mind to vow that if Washington don t resign, I will. The old hero looks very grave of late.','ltr_jod3625.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3626','letter','1796-04-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I DINED on Monday at the Presidents with young La Fayette and his preceptor, tutor or friend, whatever they call him, whose name is Frestel.','ltr_jod3626.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3627','letter','1796-04-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','They have appointed committees to correspond with the merchants in all the seaports. I expect that the citizens will also be called together in the state house yard and it is said that the gentlemen will turn out','ltr_jod3627.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3628','letter','1796-04-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE sensations of 19th April, 1775, and those of this morning, have some resemblance to each other. A prospect of foreign war and civil war in conjunction, is not very pleasant.','ltr_jod3628.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3629','letter','1796-04-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The charming letter from our son I return. I know very well all his meaning. He will see man kind in his youth.','ltr_jod3629.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3630','letter','1796-04-30','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The proceedings of Boston, New York, and Philadelphia now, compared with their in temperate folly last July or August, is a curious specimen of negotiations with foreign courts and nations by the people at large in town meetings.','ltr_jod3630.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3631','letter','1796-05-03','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','THE result of Saturday\'s debate in the House of Representatives removes all anxiety for the remainder of this session, and leaves me at liberty to ask leave to go home.','ltr_jod3631.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3632','letter','1796-11-27','Stratford','CT','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','It will purify me from all envy of Mr. Jefferson, or Mr. Pinckney, or Mr. Burr, or Mr. any body who may be chosen President or Vice President.','ltr_jod3632.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3633','letter','1796-12-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Yesterday I dined with the President, in company with John Watts, the king of the Cherokees, with a large number of his chiefs and their wives','ltr_jod3633.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3634','letter','1796-12-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','ENCLOSED are some signal accomplishments of prophecies. Be cool and discreet in your communications of them.','ltr_jod3634.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3635','letter','1796-12-30','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The President says he must sell something to en able him to clear out. When a man is about retiring from public life, and sees nothing but a ploughshare between him and the grave, he naturally thinks most upon that.','ltr_jod3635.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3636','letter','1797-01-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I DINED yesterday with Dr. Rush, who desired me to send the enclosed oration upon a weak democrat whom he is pleased to call a great philosopher, astronomer and republican.','ltr_jod3636.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3637','letter','1797-01-11','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','ON Tuesday, when I waited, as usual, on Mrs. Washington, after attending the levee, she congratulated me very complaisantly and affectionately on my election, and went farther and said more than I expected.','ltr_jod3637.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3638','letter','1797-01-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Mr. Madison is to retire. It seems the mode of becoming great is to retire. Madison, I suppose, after a retirement of a few years, is to be President or Vice President.','ltr_jod3638.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3639','letter','1797-01-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Dr. Priestley breakfasted with me. I asked him whether it was his opinion that the French would ultimately establish a republican government.','ltr_jod3639.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3640','letter','1797-02-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I HOPE you will not communicate to any body the hints I give you about our prospects ; but they appear every day worse and worse. House rent at twenty- seven hundred dollars a year...','ltr_jod3640.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3641','letter','1797-02-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I must wait to know whether Congress will do any thing or not to furnish my house. If they do not, I will have no house before next fall, and then a very moderate one, with very moderate furniture.','ltr_jod3641.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3642','letter','1797-03-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','YOUR dearest friend never had a more trying day than yesterday. A solemn scene it was indeed, and it was made more affecting to me by the presence of the General,whose countenance was as serene and unclouded as the day.','ltr_jod3642.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3643','letter','1797-03-09','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The President and Mrs. Washington go off this morning for Mount Vernon. Yesterday afternoon he came to make me his farewell visit','ltr_jod3643.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3644','letter','1797-03-11','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','If I could have my wish, there should never be a show or a feast made for the President while I hold the office. My birthday happens when Congress will never sit, so that I hope it will never be talked of.','ltr_jod3644.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3645','letter','1797-03-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I AM so constantly engaged in business, most of which is new to me, that it seems as if it was impossible to find time to write even to you ; yet I believe I write every post.','ltr_jod3645.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3646','letter','1797-03-17','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I HOPE to get into the house on Monday next, but shall purchase no nice furniture till you come. I shall make a little establishment for myself and keep bachelors hall for some time.','ltr_jod3646.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3647','letter','1797-04-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','You, and such petit maitres and maitresses as you, are forever criticising the periods and diction of such great men as presidents and chief justices. Do you think their minds are taken up with such trifles?','ltr_jod3647.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3648','letter','1797-05-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Our mother and our niece are gone to rest. The first a fruitfully ripe, the last but a blossom or a bud.','ltr_jod3648.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3649','letter','1798-11-28','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Your company here is much desired by every body, but by none so much as me.','ltr_jod3649.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3650','letter','1798-12-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I pray you to banish as much as possible all gloomy thoughts, and be very cautious to avoid every thing which may endanger a return of your old disorders.','ltr_jod3650.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3651','letter','1799-01-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I don t like this bravery which grows in proportion as danger appears to lessen. I like that fortitude which increases as danger grows, in a good cause.','ltr_jod3651.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3652','letter','1799-01-25','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Thomas is my delight and I know not how to re sign him ; but as I know you will not be quite well till you see him, I shall consent to his going next week.','ltr_jod3652.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3653','letter','1799-02-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','Thomas is to set off from New York to-day for Quincy, and I wish him a pleasant journey, which the fine weather and convenient snow promises.','ltr_jod3653.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3654','letter','1799-02-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I came home and went into a warm bed and had a fine perspiration, occasioned, I believe, by my drinking three glasses of Madeira wine at supper, and. two more after I came home','ltr_jod3654.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3655','letter','1799-10-25','Trenton','NJ','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','An election is approaching which will set us at liberty from these uncomfortable journeys','ltr_jod3655.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3656','letter','1799-10-27','Trenton','NJ','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have been, forenoon and afternoon, to church to hear Parson Waddell, who gave us two discourses good and wholesome for soul, body, and estate.','ltr_jod3656.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3657','letter','1800-10-13','Washington','MD','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I have seen many cities and fine places since you left me, and particularly Mount Vernon. Mrs. Washington and her whole family very kindly inquired after your health','ltr_jod3657.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3658','letter','1800-11-02','Washington','MD','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','I shall say nothing of public affairs. I am very glad you consented to come on, for you would have been more anxious at Quincy than here','ltr_jod3658.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jod3659','letter','1801-02-16','Washington','MD','US','John','Adams','','Abigail','Adams','','individual','','The election will be decided this day in favor of Mr. Jefferson, as it is given out by good authority.','ltr_jod3659.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of John Adams, Addressed to His Wife. Edited by His Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1841');
